      • intersect

        @Deprecated
public GroupingQuery<T> intersect(IQuery<T> intersectQuery)
        Deprecated. Do not use. Using this method could cause a performance problem. A more efficient query version should be considered. For example, if both sides of INTERSECT are querying the same table, use a single query and have the restriction be the ANDing of the restrictions from both sides of the INTERSECT.
        Intersects this query with the query passed in. The return type of the two queries must be equal.
        Specified by:
        intersect in interface IQuery<T extends Bean>
        Parameters:
        intersectQuery - the query to union with

      • union

        public GroupingQuery<T> union(IQuery<T> unionQuery)
        Unions this query with the query passed in. The return type of the two queries must be equal. The result query will not contain duplicate queries from the two sets. Union can only be done once on a query. Basically this method builds a binary tree and the result of this method is the union of this query and unionQuery.
        Specified by:
        union in interface IQuery<T extends Bean>
        Parameters:
        unionQuery - the query to union with
        Returns:
        the result query that is the union of this and the query passed in.
